The President welcomed the UConn Huskies, the 2023 NCAA Men's Basketball Champions, to the White House. He congratulated the team on their victory and praised their resilience and teamwork. The President also recognized the Second Gentleman and the Secretary of Education, who both have connections to UConn. He highlighted the team's accomplishments and their comeback throughout the season. The President emphasized the importance of sports in bringing the nation together and wished the team luck in their future endeavors. Coach Hurley thanked the President for hosting them and presented him with a UConn jersey.